              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A timing scintillator (150 mu-m).",
                "PIN diode telescope consisting of five silicon",
                "detectors (50x50 mm2), with thicknesses of 140 mu-m,",
                "140 mu-m, 500 mu-m, 1000 mu-m, and 1000 mu-m,",
                "respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Beryllium target thicknesses were 23 and 47 mg/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Heavy ions in this study have been",
                "identified by the combination of magnetic-rigidity,",
                "time-of-flight (ToF), total kinetic energy (TKE),",
                "and energy-loss measurements."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The production cross section for individual fragments",
                "was calculated as sigma = (Nf/(Nb*Nt*T))*10**27 [mb],",
                "where Nf is the number of a given fragment detected at",
                "the end of the fragment separator, Nb is the number of",
                "total incoming beam particles, T is the transmission of",
                " the fragment through the separator, and Nt is the",
                "number of target atoms (1/cm2)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A conservative estimation of error was",
                "performed by selecting the maximum, minimum, and mode",
                "of all possible transmission values for a given",
                "fragment as the upper error limit, lower error limit,",
                "and most probable transmission, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
